reviewText:
Despite watching youtubers play this game less than a year ago, I still really enjoyed playing this short indie horror game.

This game is getting mixed reviews, I would recommend this game IF you like:
* Beautiful artwork;
* Atmospheric music;
* Disturbing and confusing imagery and plot lines;
* Getting murdered many times (Limbo-style!);
* Creepy surround headphone effects.

This game plays like a maze more than anything. There aren't really puzzles to solve or enemies to battle, although you have to outsmart a few enemies by being stealthy. So don't play Neverending Nightmares if you need fights or detective work to enjoy a game.

